<h1>ğŸ§  AI-Powered Decision Support Dashboard</h1>

<p>
A <strong>production-grade, decision-first analytics system</strong> that converts raw numerical data into
<strong>clear, explainable, and actionable decisions</strong> â€” without domain assumptions, fake AI, or chart-heavy dashboards.
</p>

<p>
This project demonstrates <strong>decision intelligence</strong>, not exploratory data analysis.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>ğŸ¯ Project Objective</h2>

<p>
Most analytics tools answer:
</p>

<blockquote>
<p>â€œWhat does the data show?â€</p>
</blockquote>

<p>
This system answers:
</p>

<blockquote>
<p><strong>â€œGiven this data, what action should be taken now?â€</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<p>
It is designed for <strong>managers, founders, and analysts</strong> who need fast, trustworthy decisions.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>ğŸ§  Core Design Principles</h2>

<ul>
<li>Decision-first, not chart-first</li>
<li>Rule-based and explainable logic</li>
<li>Dataset-agnostic language</li>
<li>No black-box AI</li>
<li>One-screen executive clarity</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>âœ¨ Key Features</h2>

<h3>ğŸ”¹ Universal Dataset Support</h3>
<ul>
<li>Accepts any CSV or Excel file</li>
<li>No assumed schema or domain</li>
<li>Automatically detects numeric columns</li>
<li>Works across all dataset types</li>
</ul>

<h3>ğŸ”¹ Decision Readiness Score (0â€“100)</h3>
<ul>
<li>Single score representing decision safety</li>
<li>Derived from:</li>
<ul>
<li>Recent vs baseline change</li>
<li>Variability (stability)</li>
<li>Trend consistency</li>
<li>Data sufficiency</li>
</ul>
<li>Fully mathematical and auditable</li>
</ul>

<h3>ğŸ”¹ Priority Classification</h3>
<p>
The system assigns one clear priority:
</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>High Priority</strong> â€” Immediate attention required</li>
<li><strong>Medium Priority</strong> â€” Monitor and delay major actions</li>
<li><strong>Low Priority</strong> â€” Safe to continue cautiously</li>
</ul>

<h3>ğŸ”¹ Explainable Decision Logic</h3>
<p>
Each decision includes a <strong>â€œWhy this decision?â€</strong> section, such as:
</p>
<ul>
<li>Recent values decreased compared to baseline</li>
<li>Variability increased beyond stability threshold</li>
<li>Trend consistency weakened</li>
</ul>

<p>No hidden logic. No vague explanations.</p>

<h3>ğŸ”¹ Decision Stability Indicator</h3>
<ul>
<li>High / Medium / Low stability</li>
<li>Indicates how likely the decision is to change</li>
<li>Helps assess reliability before acting</li>
</ul>

<h3>ğŸ”¹ What-If Scenario Simulation</h3>
<ul>
<li>Interactive simulation of metric decrease</li>
<li>Interactive simulation of variability increase</li>
<li>Priority is recalculated deterministically</li>
<li>No predictive guessing</li>
</ul>

<h3>ğŸ”¹ Decision Comparison Snapshot</h3>
<ul>
<li>Side-by-side view of current vs simulated state</li>
<li>Shows priority, score, and confidence differences</li>
<li>Supports decision validation</li>
</ul>

<h3>ğŸ”¹ Neutral Recommended Actions</h3>
<ul>
<li>Increase monitoring frequency</li>
<li>Avoid decisions dependent on this metric</li>
<li>Continue current approach cautiously</li>
</ul>

<p>
All actions are <strong>dataset-agnostic</strong> and universally applicable.
</p>

<h3>ğŸ”¹ Minimal Supporting Visualization</h3>
<ul>
<li>Small, secondary trend view</li>
<li>Used only as reference</li>
<li>Decision never depends on chart interpretation</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>ğŸ–¥ï¸ UI & UX Highlights</h2>

<ul>
<li>Executive hero section at the top</li>
<li>Clear visual hierarchy</li>
<li>Decision dominates the screen</li>
<li>Collapsible sections reduce noise</li>
